    <h2>What we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Contact details and correspondence when you email us or submit enquiries.</li>
      <li>Business information you choose to share to help us understand your needs.</li>
      <li>Technical logs generated by our hosting platform (security and performance).</li>
      <li>Minimal, privacy-friendly usage analytics (see “Cookies &amp; analytics”).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we use your data (lawful bases)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> responding to enquiries; operating, securing and improving our website; maintaining business records; marketing our own services to professional contacts.</li>
      <li><strong>Legal obligations:</strong> complying with applicable laws and regulatory requirements.</li>
      <li><strong>Consent:</strong> where you opt in to updates (you can withdraw any time).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Sharing</h2>
    <p>We use trusted processors to operate our business infrastructure, including Microsoft 365 (email/document storage) and our hosting provider (Kinsta). We do not sell your personal data. We only share data where necessary for the purposes above or if required by law.</p>

    <h2>International transfers</h2>
    <p>Your data is primarily processed in the UK/EU. If processing occurs outside the UK/EU, we rely on an adequacy decision or Standard Contractual Clauses (and equivalent UK safeguards) to protect your information.</p>

    <h2>Retention</h2>
    <p>We keep enquiry correspondence and related records for as long as reasonably necessary for the purposes described above, typically up to six years, unless a longer period is required by law or to establish, exercise or defend legal rights.</p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>You have rights under UK data protection law, including to access, correct, erase, restrict or object to processing, and data portability (where applicable). You can exercise these by contacting us. You also have the right to complain to the UK Information Commissioner’s Office (<a href="https://ico.org.uk" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a>).</p>

    <h2>Cookies &amp; analytics</h2>
    <p>This site uses Kinsta’s privacy-friendly analytics and essential hosting logs to help us understand performance and detect abuse. We do not use third-party advertising cookies or cross-site tracking. You can use browser settings to control cookies.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>We may update this notice from time to time. Material changes will be reflected here with a new “Last updated” date.</p>

    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: 13 October 2025.</p>
